sentences: David Brent Nail (born May 18, 1979) is an American country music artist, and frontman of the band David Nail & The Well Ravens.
In 2002, he debuted the single "Memphis" from an unreleased album for Mercury Records Nashville.

Five years later, he signed with MCA Nashville, for which he has released four studio albums: I'm About to Come Alive, The Sound of a Million Dreams, I'm a Fire, and Fighter plus two extended plays, 1979 and Uncovered.
